    "body": "The problem with estimatesmartfee was that it isn't a wallet RPC, which is required when the reason is say, `fallbackfee` . \r\nI felt that if a user is able to call a command from the wallet itself and it uses the same functions which are used by commands like `sendtoaddress` and `sendmany` , it would minimize the possibility of a strange high feerate like  [#16072](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/16072)\r\nDo suggest what the best way to move forward would be.",
