    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I also agree with updating `estimatesmartfee` rather than a whole new rpc.\r\n\r\nWhile fallbackfee is something that only matters to wallets, it isn't tied to specific wallets (all wallets loaded will have the same fallbackfee set) so it isn't necessary to have a wallet rpc just to account for it. Instead, you could add it to `WalletClient` (have `WalletClient` also parse the `-fallbackfee` option) and retrieve it from there via `NodeContext`. When wallets are disabled, `NodeContext.wallet_client` will just be nullptr, and in that situation, `-fallbackfee` couldn't have been set and so doesn't matter for the fee estimation.",
